  "text": "Although current management guidelines for HCC do not require biopsy to prove the diagnosis [CITATION_1] , lesions greater than 2 cm on MRI or computed tomograph angiography (CTA) scans, with AFP either elevated more than 400 ng/mL or rising within sequential measurements do not require histologic confirmation according to the guidelines of the European Association for the Study of the Liver (EASL). In patients without chronic liver disease, liver biopsy is strongly recommended for the final diagnosis and proper treatment plan.",
